1883. 



                     JAMES BARRYMORE
                   was indicted

                      for stealing 2 waistcoats, value 1l.; 8 handkerchiefs, 1l.; 3 yards of serge, 7s.; 1 brush, 1s.; and 1 fur Victorine, 8s. 6d.; 


                     also, 4 yards of linen cloth, 6s.; 1 Holland coat, 4s.; 2 waistcoats, 1l.; 1 pair of boots, 10s.; 3 handkerchiefs 7s. 6d.; 1 1/2 yards of serge, 3s. 6d.; 


                     also, 1 1/2 yards of serge, 3s.; 1 pair of boots, 10s.; 37 handkerchiefs, 4l. 12s. 6d.; 12 waistcoats, 6l.; 2 coats, 3l.; 4 yards of linen cloth, 6s.; and 1 pair of trowsers, 15s.;


                      also 21 waistcoats, 10l. 10s.; 22 handkerchiefs, 2l. 15s.; and 1 pair of trowsers, 15s.;


